cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is about learning convolutional neural image representations without manual supervision using motion cues in the form of optical flow. This topic falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a simpler learning goal for embedding pixels, which can be applied to various tasks such as image classification, detection, and segmentation, indicating the relevance to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper uses deep neural networks for learning, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.RO, and cs.NE.
